(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
(1. MOTIVATION) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(Modern distributed systems are drowning in complexity. X.509) show newline
(certificates require decoder rings. Container orchestration demands) show newline
(armies of SREs. Security policies hide in YAML nested seventeen levels) show newline
(deep.) show newline
() show newline
(The Manifesto:) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    "Authorized capability set with auditing. No central authority.") show newline
() show newline
(These three principles - Simple Public Key Infrastructure \(SPKI\)) show newline
(authorization, cryptographic audit trails, and optional centralization -) show newline
(are not new. They were proven in VAXcluster security \(1984-1994\),) show newline
(proposed in Simple Distributed Security Infrastructure \(SDSI\) at) show newline
(Internet Engineering Task Force \(IETF\) 29 Seattle \(1994\), and) show newline
(implemented partially in products that didn't survive their parent) show newline
(companies. Cyberspace completes what was started.) show newline
() show newline
(Design Lineage:) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(  Era    System       Contribution                                                 ) show newline
(  1984   VAXcluster   "Behave as one" - N nodes, one security domain               ) show newline
(  1985   VMS C2       Audit trails, access control, security primitives            ) show newline
(  1993   VMS 6.0      Cluster-wide intrusion detection, TLV object store           ) show newline
(  1994   SDSI         Self-certifying keys, local names \(Rivest, IETF 29\)          ) show newline
(  1999   SPKI         Authorization certificates, capability delegation            ) show newline
(  2026   Cyberspace   Synthesis: SPKI + audit + IPv6 mesh + no central authority   ) show newline
() show newline
(DECnet Phase IV had 24-bit addressing - fatal for internet scale.) show newline
(Cyberspace is designed for IPv6: 128-bit addresses, global mesh, same) show newline
(security principles.) show newline
() show newline
(Cyberspace returns to first principles:) show newline
() show newline
(  * S-expressions for everything: readable, parseable, auditable) show newline
(  * Minimal TCB: prove the crypto, evolve the rest) show newline
(  * No central authority: SDSI/SPKI namespaces over PKI hierarchies) show newline
(  * Running code: every feature traces to research, runs, and is tested) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
