() show newline
(Rationale:) show newline
() show newline
(  * OCaml: Strong types, formal verification with Coq, compile-time safety) show newline
(  * Chicken Scheme: Interactive development, S-expressions everywhere, rapid evolution) show newline
(  * The boundary: Tiny, frozen, proven. The TCB does crypto and nothing else.) show newline
() show newline
(A smaller TCB means fewer bugs that can break security. We prove the) show newline
(crypto in Coq. Everything else can evolve freely.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(2.1 Interface Philosophy) show newline
(------------------------) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    "English on top, Scheme for everything else.") show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    +-------------------------------------------------------------+) show newline
(    |  > status                    Command mode: English verbs    |) show newline
(    |  > commit "message"          No parens needed              |) show newline
(    |  > soup                      Explore, inspect, act          |) show newline
(    +-------------------------------------------------------------+) show newline
(    |  > \(define x \(keys\)\)         Scheme mode: Full power       |) show newline
(    |  > \(map publish \(releases\)\)  Compose, transform, compute   |) show newline
(    |  > \(filter signed? certs\)    Lambda is home                |) show newline
(    +-------------------------------------------------------------+) show newline
() show newline
(The command layer is syntactic sugar. The Scheme layer is substrate.) show newline
(Users start with English, graduate to Scheme when they need composition.) show newline
(No mode switchingâ€”parens are the only delimiter.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
