(3.1 The Vault) show newline
(-------------) show newline
() show newline
(The vault is the disk.) show newline
() show newline
(In VAXcluster, multiple subsystems coordinated distributed storage: MSCP) show newline
(served disks across nodes, the DLM managed locks, SCS handled) show newline
(communication, and the quorum disk arbitrated partitions. Five) show newline
(subsystems, complex interactions, decades of refinement.) show newline
() show newline
(Cyberspace has one abstraction: the vault.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    VAXcluster          Cyberspace) show newline
(    ----------          ----------) show newline
(    Shared disk    >    Vault) show newline
(    MSCP           >    Gossip replication) show newline
(    DLM            >    Quorum consensus) show newline
(    SCS            >    CIP \(secure channels\)) show newline
(    Quorum disk    >    Vault) show newline
(    LAVC           >    Enrollment) show newline
() show newline
(The vault is content-addressed storage, replicated across nodes via) show newline
(gossip, with quorum state for partition handling:) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    \(cluster-quorum) show newline
(      \(epoch 42\)) show newline
(      \(expected-votes 5\)) show newline
(      \(quorum 3\)) show newline
(      \(members) show newline
(        \(alice \(votes 1\) \(role master\)\)) show newline
(        \(bob   \(votes 1\) \(role full\)\)) show newline
(        \(carol \(votes 1\) \(role full\)\)) show newline
(        \(dave  \(votes 1\) \(role witness\)\)) show newline
(        \(eve   \(votes 1\) \(role archive\)\)\)\)) show newline
() show newline
(Boot sequence mirrors VAXcluster: 1. Node reads local vault > knows) show newline
(expected membership 2. Contacts other expected members 3. Counts) show newline
(responding votes 4. If â‰¥ quorum > cluster forms, proceed 5. If <) show newline
(quorum > hang, wait, retry) show newline
() show newline
(Partition with quorum continues. Partition without hangs. No split-brain) show newline
(writes. When healed, minority syncs from majority. Epoch increments on) show newline
(membership change.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    $ cyberspace vault init) show newline
(    $ cyberspace vault commit -m "Deploy new API") show newline
(    $ cyberspace vault verify) show newline
(    âœ“ All signatures valid) show newline
() show newline
(Every commit is cryptographically sealed. No GPG. No separate signing) show newline
(step.) show newline
